title: [spoilers] why couldn’t the wildlings...
body:
dog through the wall at some point along the wall or even dig a tunnel underneath. There were like 19 night watch look out points; I’m not sure how many people were spread atop the wall guarding it, but we know only 3 of the 19 towers were manned. The wall runs, what like at least 300 miles or more, that’s a lot of fucking wall to cover. I’m sure the windings could have scouted a breach point on the wall and to either chip away at it or dig underneath, even if they assumed all 19 towers were manned, but a simple warg could have figured that out. I’m just confused, aside from plot issues, why they would plan for a direct assault on the wall, although they had help from the other side. They had all this time to figure out a way of breaching the wall and there was no magic holding them back, they should have at least been able to dig a tunnel. I’m not even taking about sailing around the edges; that’s a whole other head scratcher.



Source: https://ift.tt/2C8Dobg
